---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="App Privacy (nutrition labels) — QuiKey AI Hub"
  description="Reference for App Store Connect: data types collected when optional analytics is enabled, and data processed by third-party AI providers you choose."
  productName="QuiKey AI Hub"
  navLinks={[
    { href: '/aihub/', label: 'AI Hub' },
    { href: '/aihub/privacy', label: 'Privacy policy' },
    { href: '/blog', label: 'Blog' },
  ]}
  footerLinks={[
    { href: '/aihub/', label: 'AI Hub' },
    { href: '/aihub/privacy', label: 'Privacy' },
    { href: '/aihub/app-privacy-labels', label: 'App Privacy (labels)' },
    { href: '/terms', label: 'Terms' },
  ]}
>
  <section class="labels-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="labels-content">
        <h1>App Privacy — QuiKey AI Hub</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Use this page as a checklist when you complete <strong>App Privacy</strong> in App Store Connect. Wording follows
          Apple’s “nutrition label” categories. If your shipped build changes behavior, update both this page and App Store
          Connect together.
        </p>

        <h2>Data collection — summary</h2>
        <table class="label-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Category</th>
              <th>Collected?</th>
              <th>Linked to identity?</th>
              <th>Used for</th>
              <th>Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Identifiers — Device ID</strong></td>
              <td>Yes, if user enables “Send usage metrics”</td>
              <td>No (pseudonymous ID for analytics)</td>
              <td>Analytics</td>
              <td>PostHog identifies an anonymous installation; not your name or email.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Usage Data — Product interaction</strong></td>
              <td>Yes, if user enables metrics</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>Analytics</td>
              <td>Feature usage, success/failure counts; no file or chat body content.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Diagnostics</strong></td>
              <td>Yes, if user enables metrics</td>
              <td>No</td>
              <td>Analytics</td>
              <td>Error or diagnostic signals tied to events; not full system crash dumps unless separately configured.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>User content (files, text, prompts)</strong></td>
              <td>Not collected by QuiKey for analytics</td>
              <td>—</td>
              <td>—</td>
              <td>
                Content is sent <strong>only</strong> to AI providers <strong>you</strong> invoke, under their policies—not
                to a QuiKey server for storage as described in the main privacy policy.
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2>App Store Connect — walkthrough</h2>
        <ol class="steps">
          <li>
            <strong>App Privacy → Get Started.</strong> If asked whether data is collected: <strong>Yes</strong> (optional
            analytics when enabled).
          </li>
          <li>
            Add <strong>Identifiers → Device ID</strong>: Purpose <strong>Analytics</strong>. Indicate not linked to user
            identity if your answers match the table above.
          </li>
          <li>
            Add <strong>Usage Data → Product Interaction</strong>: Purpose <strong>Analytics</strong>.
          </li>
          <li>
            Add <strong>Diagnostics</strong> (if you declare any diagnostic events): Purpose <strong>Analytics</strong>.
          </li>
          <li>
            For data sent to <strong>third-party AI APIs</strong>: Apple’s form asks about data collected by <em>you</em> or
            your partners. Analytics providers count as partners for the optional metrics path. AI providers are engaged by
            the user’s in-app actions; ensure your review notes explain that users supply their own keys or accounts where
            applicable.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Encryption / export compliance</h2>
        <p>
          When you submit a build, Apple asks about encryption. This app uses standard HTTPS/TLS for network connections in
          line with Apple’s guidance for exempt-category apps. Answer based on your actual build and legal review.
        </p>

        <h2>Privacy policy URL (Mac App Store)</h2>
        <p>
          After deploy: <code>https://quikey.app/aihub/privacy</code>
        </p>

        <p class="back">
          <a href="/aihub/privacy">Full privacy policy</a> · <a href="/aihub/">AI Hub product page</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .labels-page {
    padding: 120px 0 60px;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  .labels-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .labels-content h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1f2937;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .lede {
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .labels-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1f2937;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .label-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .label-table th,
  .label-table td {
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
    color: #374151;
  }

  .label-table th {
    background: #f9fafb;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .steps {
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.75;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .steps li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .labels-content p {
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .labels-content code {
    background: #f3f4f6;
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }

  .labels-content a {
    color: #3b82f6;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .labels-content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .back {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .labels-page {
      padding: 100px 0 40px;
    }

    .label-table {
      display: block;
      overflow-x: auto;
    }
  }
</style>
